claim.claim-text:
11. A method as in one of claims 6 to 10, characterized in that in the microfluidic system (10, 210, 310) that is configured as an open network of mutually fluid-connected channels numerous channels feed into a common channel chamber. particularly designed point-like, wherein at least one of the channels functions as a measurement channel (299, 399, 400), and wherein each of the ends of the channels away from the common chamber is in contact with an electrode (297, 397, 382) that is used to exert an electrical field on the fluid, and wherein the electrodes may be supplied with electrical current and/or electrical voltage, and wherein a first electrode is assigned to a first channel and a second electrode is assigned to a second channel, characterized by the following steps: 
a) regulation of the electrical current (I2) to the value zero at the second electrode functioning as a measurement sensor; 
b) measurement of the electrical voltage (U2) at the second electrode, wherein any given voltage (U1) is applied to the first electrode; 
c) regulation of the electrical voltage (U1) at the first electrode in such a manner that the difference between U1 and U2 achieves a predetermined value.

characterized in that 
in the microfluidic system (10, 210, 310) that is configured as an open network of mutually fluid-connected channels at least four channels feed into a common channel chamber, particularly designed point-like, wherein at least one of the channels functions as a measurement channel (299, 399, 400), and wherein each of the ends of at least three channels away from the common chamber is in contact with an electrode (283, 284, 297; 382, 386, 397) that is used to exert an electrical field on the fluid, and wherein the electrodes may be supplied with electrical current and/or electrical voltage, and wherein a first electrode is assigned to a first channel, a second electrode is assigned to a second channel, and a third electrode is assigned to a third channel, characterized by the following steps: 
a) regulation of the electrical current (I2) to the value zero at the second electrode functioning as a measurement sensor; 
b) measurement of the electrical voltage (U2) at the second electrode, wherein any given voltage (U1) is applied to the first electrode; 
c) regulation of the electrical voltage (U1) at the first electrode in such a manner that the difference between U1 and U2 achieves a predetermined value; 
d) measurement of the electrical current strength (I1) at the first electrode; 
e) calculation of a nominal current (I3-nominal) at the third electrode as the sum of the current (I1) measured at the first electrode and a predetermined current (I4) assigned to the fourth channel; 
f) regulation of the current (I3) at the third electrode to the value of the previously-calculated nominal current (I3-nominal); 
g) repetition of steps b) through f).
